In Confluence, when an email is sent to a user, the notification will have the prefix to include the following:

{code}
[Confluence] Space name > Page Name > Time
{code}

In different situations, having the ability to customize the prefix (to include pages/spaces, or, change the information displayed) could be very useful for the users so it can be also adapted to the company of the user. This is a suggestion to allow Confluence Cloud to customize the email subject prefix.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}

h3. Problem Definition
If more than one user is editing an Office file with the *Atlassian Companion*, multiple versions of the document shouldn't be created as the other version isn't incorporating any changes of another user.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-39428].
  {panel}

In Confluence, we have the option to download all attachments for pages through *Page Tools > Attachments* and then, *Download All*. 

Similar as [this older request|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-5669], this will be a new one to provide the users an option to download all attachments for a Confluence instance through the UI, instead of using external alternatives.

h3. Issue Summary

When defining a  {{dynamicContentMacro}} and invoking

{code}
AP.confluence.getMacroBody(function(data){
    alert(`AP.confluence.getMacroBody - ${JSON.stringify(data)}`);
});
{code}

in page edit mode of the new Confluence editor, no body is returned in the callback function unlike the old editor. 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Spawn a connect app with a dynamicContent
# In the macro's js add this code:
{code}
AP.confluence.getMacroBody(function(data){
    alert(`AP.confluence.getMacroBody - ${JSON.stringify(data)}`);
});
{code}
# Add the macro in a blog (which forces the user to use the new Confluence editor)
# Add something inside the macro and edit the macro
# No body is returned, see comparison
* New editor:
 !Screen Shot 2019-01-09 at 9.48.45 AM.png|thumbnail! 
* Old editor:
 !Screen Shot 2019-01-09 at 9.48.01 AM.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Expected Results

The macro body is returned

h3. Actual Results

An empty body is returned in the callback function

h3. Notes

The function returns a macro body when in page view mode:

 !Snip20190108_37.png|thumbnail! 
References:
* https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/confluence/jsapi/confluence/

h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
